  <brief_title>Treximet (Sumatriptan/Naproxen Sodium), Formerly Known as Trexima, In The Acute Treatment Of Multiple Migraine Attacks</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Randomized, Double-blind, Multi-center, Placebo-controlled, Cross-over Study to Determine the Consistency of Response for Trexima (Sumatriptan 85mg/Naproxen Sodium 500mg) Administered During the Mild Pain Phase for the Acute Treatment of Multiple Migraine Attacks</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>GlaxoSmithKline</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>GlaxoSmithKline</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the consistency of response for Treximet
      (sumatriptan/naproxen sodium), formerly known as Trexima, when treating four acute migraine
      attacks at the mild pain phase and within 1 hour of onset of head pain.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
